item.title: Fixing nulls
item.dc:creator: @GrimReapersScythe GrimReapersScythe
item.description:
@GrimReapersScythe wrote:

Nulls are items id’s that aren’t specified in the source. To remove nulls (not including cached models) you need to add a model dump, of runescape’s items, into the class8. Nulls above 9000, are usually items not specified, or models in the client, that haven’t been added server sided.
